            <p>
            We would like our peers to peer with both our routers at the AMS-IX, LINX and/or NL-IX. Please configure all of the sessions the same, we will be announcing our routes with different metric values.    
            <h1 class=peering>Announcements</h1>
            BIT announces the following AS-sets: <a href="https://apps.db.ripe.net/search/query.html?searchtext=as-bit">AS-BIT</a> on IPv4 and <a href="https://apps.db.ripe.net/search/query.html?searchtext=as-bit6">AS-BIT6</a> on IPv6. Both objects are registered in the <a href="http://www.ripe.net">RIPE</a> database. Please use a maximum prefix number of at least 100 for IPv4 and at least 40 for IPv6.
            <p>
            Peers, routing policies and Communities used by BIT are documented in the <a href="https://apps.db.ripe.net/search/query.html?searchtext=as12859&flags=&sources=RIPE_NCC&grssources=&inverse=&types=">AS12859</a> object in the RIPE database.
            <h1 class=peering>Peers</h1>
            A list of all configured peers can be found <a href="/peering/peerlist.php">here</a>.
